description: This operation exports search results of a search job to a specified destination S3 bucket.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The next item following a partial list of returned backups included in a search job. For example, if a request is made to return MaxResults number of backups, NextToken allows you to return more items in your list starting at the location pointed to by the next token.

nested_items.name: ExportJobs
nested_items.description: The operation returns the included export jobs.

nested_items.name: ExportJobIdentifier
nested_items.description: This is the unique string that identifies a specific export job.

nested_items.name: ExportJobArn
nested_items.description: This is the unique ARN (Amazon Resource Name) that belongs to the new export job.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The status of the export job is one of the following:

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: This is a timestamp of the time the export job was created.

nested_items.name: CompletionTime
nested_items.description: This is a timestamp of the time the export job compeleted.

nested_items.name: StatusMessage
nested_items.description: A status message is a string that is returned for an export job.

nested_items.name: SearchJobArn
nested_items.description: The unique string that identifies the Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the specified search job.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The next item following a partial list of returned backups included in a search job.
